      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Needs improvement\" is a more direct and often harsher phrase, typically implying that current performance is falling below acceptable standards. In contrast, \"has developmental opportunities\" is softer and frames the feedback around growth, suggesting potential that hasn't been fully realized yet. Using the latter is generally recommended for constructive conversations, as it focuses on future growth rather than past failures.",
      "source": "target",
